    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In similar situations, I have found useful the comment, ''I am surprised that you would say that.'' When the offender says something to the effect, ''What did I say?'' I reply, ''You know what you said, and you look much more intelligent than your comment or your question.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In similar situations, I have found useful the comment, ''I am surprised that you would say that.'' When the offender says something to the effect, ''What did I say?'' I reply, ''You know what you said, and you look much more intelligent than your comment or your question.''</p>
        <p>My rule is to never debate their original statement, just to insist that they are not as stupid as it sounded. It often leaves them sputtering and defused.</p>
        <p>Richard L. Phillips  New York</p>
      </block>
